description:
Kyle Rayner returns to Earth with Jordan's coffin, the battery and dreadful warning. A terrible menace is approaching and it is yellow.

Overview

Hal Jordan was one of the greatest heroes in the DCU until tragedy turned him into one of its greatest villains. Today, his soul searches for redemption as the Spectre. But redemption may not be what Jordan himself needs...or wants. The fates of Kyle Rayner, John Stewart, Guy Gardner, and the rest of the Green Lantern mythology unfold in this colossal tale of heroism involving the entire DCU!
name: Blackest Night

description: Persha and the council of House Dexter work on reuniting the two Houses. Ingra with her army tries to take back House Sinister. Trenin finds out he cant kill Seahn. With the powers of Pyrem, Seahn, Persha, and Orium Altwaal is woken. Altwaal reunites the two houses and kills Persha for killing Seahn.

Giselle is going to every Guild to show them she deserves the powers of the Eternal Masters.  When she visits the Djinn Guild, Atyaah tells her to tell him stories. They tell each other stories back and forth, until Giselle figures out he is actually Iblis, a ancient evil Djinn. She fights him and release Atyaah.

Giselle goes to the Astral Guild. There is a geek there who takes away peoples power to astral project which keeps them comatose in their own bodies. Giselle quickly disposes of him and saves all of the people in the Astral Guild.
Giselle visits the Tantric Guild. Only to be blamed for killing some of the residents. Giselle finds out it is the work of a succubus.
Giselle is teleported to a place where there are caveman and dinosaurs. Genevieve, Skitter and the rest of the Guild Masters don't know where she is.

Giselle figures out the caveman she was protecting from the monkey men were sacrificing children. While the monkey men were trying to save the children. The dark magi spirit finds a way to escape giselle and went back to the Dark Magi Master.

Giselle can't use her powers anymore. Skitter finds Giselle. Vashua is working with the Dark Magi. The people of Ciress figure out that the Guild Masters don't have the eternal spirits anymore, and start to riot the Guild Masters buildings.

Giselle makes it back to Ciress. Only to hear from the eternal spirits the Dark Magi eternal spirit has escaped. Genevieve tries to calm the crowd of people furios at her for lying. Giselle goes help Yinma of her "men" problems.
Giselle goes to the Dark Magi Guild to see how he got the eternal spirit back. She runs into a man who says he's destined to become the next Dark Magi.

On a world where society is based upon magic instead of technology, ultimate power rests in the hands of the last person who wants it. Party-girl Giselle Villard couldn't care less about magic until a mysterious symbol on her palm made her the mystic protector of planet Ciress. Now she must mature into her new role before a legion of newfound enemies can destroy her! Giselle's adventure in the land of the Dark Magi Guild concludes as she is caught between the most evil sorcerer on Ciress and the mysterious crusader named Tancred, who seeks to bring down the rule of the Dark Magi! Wiping out Black Magic would be a good thing, right? Guess again!    
 
 
Giselle tries to help the new man she meet. She made an oath with the Dark Magi not to kill him so he doesnt. Vashua the Tantric Guild Master comes in and kills the man.
name: Beyond Good And Evil

description:
Babe Behind Bars! Giselle is held prisoner by her most insidious enemy ever: the super- secret Geometer Guild. This group, which has secretly controlled much of the history of planet Ciress for centuries, has discovered a way to render our mighty Mystic powerless. Without her magical might, does Giselle have what it takes to wind the day? And who is that mysterious cellmate of hers...?     
 
Giselle is captured by Archemus the master of a secret guild called the Geometer Guild. Giselle while in prison meets no other than Darrow. Archemus with his staff he can cancel any kind of magic. Vashua has called a Guild Master meeting, but tricking them and capturing them. They all go to the Geometer Guild building.
name: Crunching Numbers

description:
Giselle's greatest victory, with the most unlikely ally, begins here! Panic rules the streets as Geomancer Guild's Master Archemus prepares to reshape the entire world of Ciress! Meanwhile, Giselle is locked in a dungeon, without of her magical powers!    
 
Giselle learns the history of the Geometer Guild. Archemus kills all of the Dark Magi people. But brings them back to life so Magus can rule without intervention.
name: Babe Behind Bars

description:
This is it, the culmination of a year long saga! Battered and bruised, Giselle must use every magical lesson she's learned to escape her imprisonment and bring down the evil Geometer Guild!    
 
Giselle escapes and with the help of Darrow and Magus defeats Archemus. Magus kills Archemus with no fuss from anyone.
name: Bare-Knuckle Brawl

description:
Giselle and her erstwhile ally travel to the Tantric Lands on the trail of the traitorous Vashua...but can she trust the mystery man leading the hunt?     
 
 Darrow, Skitter, and Giselle goes to the Tantric Guild to kind Vashua. Vashua has switched bodies wiht another person. Giselle finds her and put her in her rightfull body. When Giselle leaves there's trouble in the form of Solusandra, looking for her sigil.
name: Tantric Trouble

description:
No Sigil...no magic? How can Giselle defeat the savage snow dragon if she no longer possesses her sorcery skills?    
 
Giselle goes back to Ciress to help her sister defend the Guild building. From Magus undead army. Giselle with the help of her sister wins. Samandahl Rey comes to Giselle and tells her a war is coming and they need her. So she departs with him.(Last Issue)
name: Untitled

description:
Will Giselle lose her Sigil? First she stole Brath's mark of power ? now Solusandra has come to Ciress seeking the source of our hero's magical might! Be there as Giselle faces a shocking turning point!    
 
Solusandra wants her sigil back and fights Giselle for it. She gets what she wants and goes away. The eternal spirits are set free into the Guild Masters bodies. Skitter tells Giselle to go back to the place where the Geometer guild erased all magic.
name: Untitled

description: Space may be infinite, but Sam's trapped by an army of pursuers! They may not know about Sam's new ability to change the shape of things, but they're about to get a first-hand demonstration when Sam applies that talent to some formerly small-scale weapons. That opening leads him to another... a chance to take on his Saurian nemesis, Loser, face to face!

Return of the Yeti! Giselle once again journeys to the prehistoric realm for a team-up with the wise and wooly Yeti! Together, they must destroy the arcane artifact that keeps magic from working in this lost land-but first they'll have to defeat the Snow Dragon that guards it!     
 
Giselle tries to bring magic back to a place where magic was wiped clean.
name: Snow Dragon!

description: Sam suddenly finds himself face to face with an unexpected adversary. His name is Trenin the Hunter, and he's here to win Sam over to his cause... or kill him. Meanwhile, the Saurian prince, Loser, has captured the BitterLuck and boards Sam's ship to rescue the Sultan's missing wife, but he's about to find out that Zanni doesn't intend to be taken back alive.

Sam's strange encounter with Trenin has left him with a magnificent new ship and a tight deadline. Can he reach the Saurian homeworld in time to keep Roiya from being disassembled and Zanni from being sent home to the Sultan? Meanwhile, Loser shows Zanni all the hospitality the Saurians have to offer visiting royalty... isolation, enforced by a lethal security system.

The sentient BitterLuck waits in Saurian space, trying to hide behind a small moon. That is until Prince Tchlusarud orders the secret surveillance on the small ship changed into an execution! Now, Roiya and the BitterLuck have to outmaneuver a squad of Saurian cutwings... Meanwhile, Zanni, JeMerik and Sam are all down on the surface of Tcharun, with Sam finally taking his shot at Loser in a long-awaited fight to the death!

A pampered princess, fleeing from an abusive spouse... or is there something more to Zanniati's escape from Tanipal? The answer is revealed when Sam brings her back to her homeworld on his new ship, which also carries JeMerik Meer... and Roiya! Meanwhile, Loser finds he has yet another reason for wanting revenge...

Sam's absence is felt across the battlefield as Roiya does her best to lead the Union Army to victory. Meanwhile, on a planet far away, Sam faces an entirely different kind of war ? but one with stakes just as momentous and just as deadly.

With the Union Army on the brink of defeat, they find themselves indefensible without Sam and pray for his return. Unfortunately, Sam is somewhere new, and the stranger he meets there will not only drop Sam's jaw, but yours, as well!

Chuck Dixon explodes into the CrossGen Universe and takes over as new Sigil scribe with the adventures of Zanni, assassin! She's on a solo mission to save Delassia by taking out the man who ordered the siege on her world. Meanwhile, Roiya and JeMerik are all that's between the Union President and a deadly female Saurian hit team, and Sam is still... missing.

Sam returns just in time to save... who? Zanni is the captive of her vengeful husband and learns of a terrible weapon developed by the Saurians to destroy the Planetary Union. Roiya and JeMerik face the deadly Saurian sisters who are willing to die themselves to wreak maximum damage. Loser is a captive of Khyradon and faces a fate worse than extermination.

The Saurian Empire strikes its most daring blow yet in its war with the human race. An unusual weapon of incredible destruction is launched at the very homeworld of the Planetary Union. Sam must balance billions of lives in jeopardy against the life of Zanni, the woman he loves.

In the aftermath of the horrific attack on Gaia, Sam and Zanni are reunited... almost. Roiya suffers a (literal) existential crisis and the Planetary Union girds for total war on the Saurian Empire. Plus, Loser is freed from captivity by... who?

Loser must choose between victory and death! An all-battle issue as Loser allies himself with nomadic rebels in opposition to the despotic Khyradon and the Matriarch herself! But first he needs an army and so must fight a desperate battle in Tcharun's most desolate clime to free an army of murderers!

WAR!!! What is it good for? In this instance it's the only way to end the threat of Khyradon and his fanatics. Sam and the crew of the BitterLuck battle their way to the surface of the Saurian homeworld while, at the same time, Loser leads a bloody revolt. Once again the bitterest of enemies share the same deadly agenda. Khyradon has another terrible weapon aimed at the heart of mankind, but will the Planetary Union's retaliation prove even more destructive?

It's the Saurians vs. the Negation in the most intense space battle yet! The universe you love to hate has engulfed a Saurian outworld, and now it's up to Tchlusarud and his most wicked warriors to save the planet! But no one told the Negation to fight fair, so expect writer Chuck "Mr. Action" Dixon to pull out all the stops!
He's a battle-scarred soldier who just wants to live his life out of the spotlight...but to save the universe from the horrors of the Negation, Sam will have to make a huge decision!

Emergency evacuation! When Sam reunites with Zanni on her home world of Delassia, it should be a happy day, right? So how come no one is smiling? Maybe it's because Sam is forcing the planet's population to flee! So why is he doing this ? and what is Zanni's secret? Plus: the return of Trouble!
A hate/hate relationship explodes in this all-action issue! Trapped on a Saurian world that's been conquered by the Negation, Loser and Vega face an even deadlier threat: each other!

The miniseries continues as the JLA guest-stars! Hal Jordan searches for his next role as he pays a visit to his old airfield. But what's happening to Guy Gardner, Coast City and Kilowog? The JLA wants answers... now!
name: Enemies Within

description:
Overview

Supergirl's impossible quest leads her to break a criminal out of jail and force him to plumb the secrets of recurring life. But while her aim may be true, her grasp of the situation is less so, leading her into battle with a deadly new foe!

Kara visits the boy she promised she'd save in the hospital while he's sleeping. She takes a few strands of hair to give Dr. Luzano a DNA sample. When she returns to their temporary base, she finds Luzano and the Resurrection Man bickering as Luzano was about to stick him with a needle while he was sleeping. Luzano tells Supergirl that the nanomachines he's built is easy. The hard part is tailoring them to the boy's genetic code.

Resurrection Man expresses his concern over allowing Luzano to work. Supergirl says that maybe he's not trusted because he never had the chance to prove himself.

After Kara finishes covering their place in lead (so Superman can't find them), she asks Resurrection Man why he isn't the happiest man alive since he can't die. He hesitates to answer then says Luzano is up to something. They check on him and Resurrection Man points out that Luzano's used the nanotech on himself. Luzano tells him to shut up and blasts him with some implants he's created. He also has the strength to punch Supergirl through a wall. Supergirl isn't too happy that he used all this time to help himself rather than saving the boy. She starts letting loose on him until Resurrection Man comes to. He tells Luzano to stops and tries blasting him. It turns out he now has developed the power to heal.

Supergirl realizes that if Resurrection Man dies now, he'll have a power other than healing. Luzano makes a move towards him and Kara hits him with her heat vision. She apologizes and punches him through his stomach. With all the work he's done to himself, he survives but is out of commission. She picks up R-Man and blasts a hole in the ceiling saying Superman will arrive for him.

In the air, Superman finds them immediately. She tells him she has to do this. Resurrection Man should be able to save the boy now. Superman says it won't work. The boy is dead.
name: Way of the World, Part Two

description: "Good For The Soul" concludes with a bang- or a splat- as a reluctant Hughie takes on the resurrected Blarney Cock in a no-holds barred brawl for it all. Annie January tells A-Train the long and the short of things, Mother's Milk continues to mystify, and Butcher provides some much-needed advice on funeral arrangements. And will Hughie ever be allowed to forget his "facial incident"?
name: Good for the Soul, Conclusion

description: IDW Publishing teams up with Gold Eagle to reprise one of adventure fiction’s longest-running novel series: Don Pendleton's Mack Bolan, The Executioner! The inspiration for countless payback warrior characters since 1969, Bolan returns in an explosive five-issue miniseries that pits him against enemies drawn from the Executioner's many novelized conflicts—from his war against the Mafia to his battles with the KGB and even today’s terrorists! By celebrated author Douglas Wojtowicz, writer of many of The Executioner novels, with art by S.L. Gallant (Johnny Quest) and a cover by Rogue Angel cover artist Rebecca A. Wrigley.
name: The Devil's Tools #1

description: Stormwatch is forced to battle Helspont and his troops and they find the battle to be almost too much for the super hero team. Synergy is called to an assembly of her superiors to figure out what a backup plan would be if Stormwatch is to fail. Her superiors tell her that they are going to free the Warguard, even if they are psychotic and uncontrollable. Despot, the leader of the Warguard, takes his group and flee to the moon, instead of helping the world fight Helspont. Stormwatch gives chase to Helspont to the Dreadnought, the space ship that Helspont is trying to retrieve. Arriving there, they also find the WildC.A.T.S as well. Savant, Union and Mr. Majestic were already at the spot and have uncovered the Dreadnought, which is revealed to be the Kherubim space craft.
name: Wildstorm Rising: Part 9

description: The Man with no name is being hunted by the United States for treason...some mess about blowing up a bridge. Soldiers are the least of his worries though as a group of killers are chasing him for a sack of gold he happened to steal. Add to this a dying padre's last request to help the mission...what will our man with no name do next?
name: Sinners and Saints Chapter One

description:
Overview

Who is the Red Mask? Jonah Hex has been hired to track down and eliminate this elusive thief...but will he succeed before the Red Mask can claim another victim? Featuring stunning art by Paulo Siqueira and Amilton Santos (BLACK CANARY) and a cover by the legendary Richard Corben!
name: The Red Mask

description:
Overview

After a seemingly endless war, things are getting even worse for the planets of Rann and Thanagar. A long-forgotten religious cult has resurfaced on Thanagar, and the people of Rann still worship the deadly Lady Styx. To make matters worse, a fanatic strapped with explosives threatens to upset the delicate balance between the two planets, setting in motion events that will once again bring together DC's greatest cosmic heroes: Adam Strange, Comet, Starfire, Hawkman, Starman, Chief Justice Max, Tigorr, the Weird and many more!

Written by the legendary Jim Starlin (Death of the New Gods, Infinity War) with art by Ron Lim (Silver Surfer) and Rob Hunter (Teen Titans), Rann/Thanagar: Holy War is an interstellar adventure that can't be missed
name: The Dawning

description:
1.  Out of the mysterious night comes the breath taking Blonde Phantom! In a Sinister setting of intrigue and violence, she dares to aid Mark Mason, Ace O.S.S. Agent when they join forces against the most cunning master-plotter of our age, the evil Signor Korte! Follow the glamorous blonde beauty as she fearfully learns that "The Atom Spells Doom!"

  2. A cunning oriental and his constant companion, a punch packing american boy, Mr. Wu and Alfie step in when a mad killer strikes. They will investigate the baffling case of "Murder At Midnight!"

  3. When accidental death comes to 7 beautiful and wealthy brides, Miss America, always on the alert for crime, gets curious! But never did she suspect modern blue-beard to wangle himself into her own family in "Unlucky Seven"

  4. Once again the beautiful Blonde Phantom, lady of mystery, plunges into perilous adventures as the joins Mark Mason in a thrill packed journey to South America in search of the elusive key to a mystery in "The Scarlet Scorpion!"
name: The Atom Spells Doom!
